        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 12:45PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 1245 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Frenchman Lake, or 8 miles north of Chilcoot, moving northeast at 55
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Frenchman Lake, Big Cove Campground, Frenchman Campground, Spring
Creek Campground, and Chilcoot Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
